This was in accordance with the early custom, afterwards dropped, that in civil juris- diction each should have supreme authority by turns, and that as a symbolos this the fasces should be borne by the lictors before one only at a time. Cf. Cie. de Rep. 11. 31. 55 (Poplicola) instituit primus, ut sinyulis consulibus alternis mensibus lic- tores praeirent. So Livy 111. 33. 6, eo die penes praefectum juris fasces duodecim erant. J. Caesar re-introduced the old for- mality. cf. Suet. Caes. 20, antiquum retulit morem, ut quo
